# Common Module Boundaries

## Required Orchestration
- For substantive work under `common/**`, first invoke `.cursor/skills/common-module-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.
- If the change also affects a feature or app root wiring, finish with `.cursor/skills/repo-verification-orchestrator/SKILL.md`.

## Placement rules
- Put cross-feature runtime abstractions in `common/core-*`.
- Put reusable Compose UI building blocks in `common/uikit`.
- Put platform-agnostic presentation helpers in `common/core-ui`.
- Put shared persistence infrastructure in `common/persistence/persistence-database`.
- Put app-wide assets or metadata in `common/resources` and `common/app-info`.
- Do not place feature-specific business logic in `common/**`.

## Dependency boundaries
- `common/core-*` modules must stay feature-agnostic.
- Shared modules must not depend on `features/**`.
- Prefer inward-facing abstractions and `expect/actual` over platform-specific leakage into shared code.
- Keep dependency direction consistent with the repository architecture:
  - UI and app layers may depend on shared modules,
  - shared modules must not depend on feature modules.

## Change review expectations
- When changing DI or navigation primitives in `common/**`, review their consumers in `composeApp` and affected features.
- When changing threading, networking, or persistence foundations, verify representative feature modules that consume them.
- Prefer small focused modules over broad utility dumping grounds.
